                  d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
              Conversion Analytics
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Track lead-to-meeting and meeting-to-customer conversion rates
              across campaigns and sources. Identify bottlenecks and optimize
              conversion funnel systematically.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern
            id="features-grid"
            width="32"
            height="32"
            patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
          >
            <path
              d="M 32 0 L 0 0 0 32"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1"></path>
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#features-grid)"></rect>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          Turn Booking Forms into Lead Generation Engines
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Lead management transforms scheduling from simple appointment
            booking into comprehensive lead capture and qualification system.
            Custom form fields collect qualification data beyond basic contact
            information, gathering budget ranges, project timelines,
            decision-making authority, and specific needs. This enriched data
            flows directly into lead scoring system that automatically
            categorizes prospects as Hot, Warm, or Cold based on qualification
            criteria. Sales teams immediately understand which leads warrant
            urgent follow-up and which need further nurturing before sales
            conversations, eliminating guesswork about prospect readiness.
          </p>

          <p>
            Campaign source tracking connects every lead back to originating
            marketing touchpoint. Whether prospects arrive via Google ads,
            LinkedIn campaigns, email sequences, or content marketing, CalendHub
            tracks source attribution automatically. This visibility reveals
            which marketing investments generate highest-quality leads versus
            those producing low-conversion traffic. Marketing teams optimize
            budget allocation based on actual lead quality and conversion data
            rather than vanity metrics like click-through rates that don't
            correlate with revenue generation.
          </p>

          <p>
            Lead assignment rules ensure prompt follow-up by routing leads to
            appropriate team members automatically. Configure assignment based
            on territory, industry vertical, deal size, product interest, or
            expertise match. When qualified lead submits booking form, system
            immediately assigns ownership and notifies designated sales
            representative. This automation eliminates manual lead distribution
            overhead and prevents leads from sitting unassigned while sales
            managers manually review queue and make assignment decisions during
            busy periods.
          </p>

          <p>
            Automated follow-up sequences maintain consistent communication
            without requiring manual effort from sales teams. Trigger email
            nurture campaigns when leads take specific actions like booking
            meetings, rescheduling, completing discovery calls, or requesting
            proposals. These touchpoint sequences keep leads engaged throughout
            buying journey while sales representatives focus time on high-value
            conversations rather than routine follow-up communications.
            Conversion analytics reveal which touchpoints and sequences drive
            meetings toward closed deals, enabling continuous optimization of
            engagement approach based on outcome data.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Badge -->
        <div
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-orange-500/10 border border-orange-500/20 rounded-full px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 mb-6"
        >
          <svg
            class="w-4 h-4"
            fill="none"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
          </svg>
          <span>How It Works</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Heading -->
        <h2
          class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6 text-text"
        >
          From Capture to Conversion
          <br />
          <span class="text-text-muted">Automated Lead Workflow</span>
        </h2>

        <!-- 3 Step Cards -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <div class="group relative">
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 rounded-3xl blur-xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
            >
            </div>
            <div
              class="relative bg-surface/80 dark:bg-surface/50 backdrop-blur-sm border border-border hover:border-orange-500/50 rounded-3xl p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-2 h-full"
            >
              <div
                class="w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-orange-600 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 shadow-lg shadow-orange-500/25"
              >
                <span class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-white">1</span
                >
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
                Design Capture Forms
              </h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Add custom fields collecting qualification data. Configure
                scoring rules assigning Hot, Warm, or Cold categories based on
                prospect responses.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <div class="group relative">
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 rounded-3xl blur-xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
            >
            </div>
            <div
              class="relative bg-surface/80 dark:bg-surface/50 backdrop-blur-sm border border-border hover:border-orange-500/50 rounded-3xl p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-2 h-full"
            >
              <div
                class="w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-orange-600 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 shadow-lg shadow-orange-500/25"
              >
                <span class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-white">2</span
                >
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
                Automatic Assignment
              </h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
                System routes leads to appropriate team members based on
                territory, expertise, or criteria you configure. Sales reps
                receive immediate notifications.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <div class="group relative">
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 rounded-3xl blur-xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
            >
            </div>
            <div
              class="relative bg-surface/80 dark:bg-surface/50 backdrop-blur-sm border border-border hover:border-orange-500/50 rounded-3xl p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-2 h-full"
            >
              <div
                class="w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-orange-600 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 shadow-lg shadow-orange-500/25"
              >
                <span class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-white">3</span
                >
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
                Track Conversions
              </h3>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Monitor lead progression from capture through meetings to closed
                deals. Identify highest-converting sources and optimize
                marketing investment accordingly.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Technical Details Card -->
        <div class="group relative">
          <div
            class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 rounded-3xl blur-xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
          >
          </div>
          <div
            class="relative bg-surface/80 dark:bg-surface/50 backdrop-blur-sm border border-border hover:border-orange-500/50 rounded-3xl p-8 transition-all duration-300"
          >
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
              Intelligent Lead Scoring Engine
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Lead scoring evaluates multiple data points simultaneously to
              categorize prospect quality. Budget range, project timeline,
              decision authority, specific requirements, company size, and
              industry vertical all factor into scoring calculation. Configure
              scoring thresholds matching your qualification criteria - perhaps
              prospects with six-figure budgets and three-month timelines
              automatically rate as Hot leads while those exploring options
              without defined budgets categorize as Cold. Scoring rules can
              consider form completion behavior too, with prospects who fill
              comprehensive qualification fields demonstrating higher engagement
              than those providing minimal information. This multi-factor
              approach produces more accurate lead prioritization than
              single-metric scoring, ensuring sales teams focus effort on
              prospects most likely to convert into revenue-generating
              customers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern
